{{Infobox motorsport championship | logo = | pixels = | caption = | category = [[Sportscar racing|Sportscar]] | country/region = {{Flagicon|GBR}} [[United Kingdom]] | inaugural = 1964 | inaugural2 = | folded = 1976 | drivers = | teams = | constructors = | engines = | tyres = | champion driver = | champion team = | manufacturer = | website = }} The '''British Sports Car Championship''', was a British domestic motor racing championship which was originally created for sports cars complying with Appendix C of the International Sporting Code.<ref>[http://www.racingsportscars.com/covers/_Goodwood-1964-03-30s.jpg Official Programme, Goodwood International Motor Racing, Easter Monday 1964, www.racingsportscars.com] Retrieved 22 May 2017</ref> <ref>[http://www.racingsportscars.com/covers/_Brands_Hatch-1965-08-30e.jpg Official Programme, Guards International Brands Hatch, 30 August 1965, www.racingsportscars.com] Retrieved 22 May 2017</ref> For 1966 the championship was for [[Group 7 (racing)|Group 7 Sports Racing Cars]] <ref>[http://www.racingsportscars.com/covers/_Brands_Hatch-1966-08-29e.jpg Programme, Guards International Trophy, Brands Hatch, 29 August 1966, www.racingsportscars.com] Retrieved 22 May 2017</ref> and for 1967 it was restricted to [[Group 4 Sports Cars]].<ref>[http://www.racingsportscars.com/covers/_Brands_Hatch-1967-08-28e.jpg Programme, Evening News International Trophy, Brands Hatch, 28 August 1967, www.racingsportscars.com] Retrieved 22 May 2017</ref> By 1970, the 2-litre sports category had become very popular across Europe, therefore the organisers decided to change the championship regulations, admitting only these cars. The championship was abandoned during the 1972 season, after one race, because of a lack of entries. An attempt to re-launch the championship lead to a one-off single season being run in 1976.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.racingsportscars.com/championship/British%20Sports%20Car%20Championship.html |title=British Sports Car Championship - Championships |publisher=Racing Sports Cars |date= |accessdate=2014-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://wsrp.ic.cz/bscc.html |title=World Sports Racing Prototypes - British Sports Car Championship |publisher=Wsrp.ic.cz |date= |accessdate=2014-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140227223242/http://www.wsrp.ic.cz/bscc.html# |archive-date=2014-02-27 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
The series began in 1964 with the Lavant Cup at [[Goodwood Motor Racing Circuit|Goodwood]] being won by [[John Coundley]], however by the end of the inaugural season, established Formula One drivers were taking part, with the reigning World Drivers Champion, [[Jim Clark]] and [[Bruce McLaren]] among the race winners.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://wsrp.ic.cz/bscc.html |title=World Sports Racing Prototypes - British Sports Car Championship |publisher=Wsrp.ic.cz |date= |accessdate=2014-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140227223242/http://www.wsrp.ic.cz/bscc.html# |archive-date=2014-02-27 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
