{{Infobox recurring event | name = GirlsAward | logo = | image = | imagesize = | caption = | genre = Clothing and fashion exhibitions | date = | frequency = Semi-annually | location = [[Tokyo]], Japan | first = 2010 | founder_name = GirlsAward executive committee | prev = <!-- [[previous event]] --> | next = <!-- [[next event]] --> | participants = | attendance = 34,000 (2014 A/W)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mdpr.jp/fashion/detail/1426525|script-title=ja:佐々木希、藤井リナ、菜々緒ら豪華競演 歴代テラハも涙で集結「Girls Award 2014 A／W」＜写真特集＞|date=2014-10-01|accessdate=2016-10-24|publisher=modelpress|language=Japanese}}</ref> | area = | budget = | people = | member = | sponsors = {{plainlist| *[[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Japan)|Ministry of Foreign Affairs]], *[[Tokyo Metropolitan Government]] *[[Fuji Television]] }} | website = {{URL|http://girls-award.com/}} | footnotes = }} {{nihongo|'''GirlsAward'''|ガールズアワード}}, sometimes abbreviated as '''GA''', is a semi-annual fashion and music event held at [[Yoyogi National Gymnasium|Yoyogi National Gymnasium 1st Gymnasium]] in [[Tokyo]], Japan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yomiuri.co.jp/adv/economy/release/detail/00240582.html|script-title=ja:株式会社Candeeが企画・制作、「GirlsAward 2016 AUTUMN/WINTER by マイナビ」の様子を、会場の代々木第一体育館から生中継！|accessdate=2016-10-24|publisher=The Yomiuri Shimbun|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref name="tokyohive20120728">{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2012/07/a-nation-and-girlsaward-joining-efforts-for-collaboration-fashion-show|title=a-nation and GirlsAward joining efforts for collaboration fashion show|date=2012-07-28|accessdate=2016-10-24|publisher=6Theory Media, LLC|work=tokyohive}}</ref> It is one of the biggest fashion events in Japan, with approximately 30,000 people attending each time. It is organized by GirlsAward Inc. under the slogan "Shibuya to Asia, and the World" and sponsored by [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Japan)|Ministry of Foreign Affairs]], [[Tokyo Metropolitan Government]] and [[Fuji Television]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rbbtoday.com/release/prtimes2-today/20160908/164253.html|script-title=ja:GirlsAward 2016 AUTUMN/WINTER by マイナビ第七弾情報解禁!!sweet× FOUR SIS & CO. スペシャルステージが追加発表!マイナビが特別協賛に決定!|accessdate=2016-10-24|publisher=IID, Inc.|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.excite.co.jp/News/fashion/20140419/Fashioncollection_5124.html|script-title=ja:FLOWER PALLETをテーマにGirlsAward 2014開幕|date=2014-04-19|accessdate=2016-10-24|publisher=Excite Japan Co., Ltd.|language=Japanese}}</ref> Usually, the Autumn/Winter(A/W) event is held in September to October, and the Spring/Summer(S/S) is held in March to May of each year.
== History ==
On September 9, 2009, the first event Girls Award 2009 was held at [[Shibuya O-East]]. It featured models, [[gravure idols]], and auditions associated with DAM [[Karaoke]] system.<ref name="itopix">{{cite web|url=http://itopix.jp/2009_09/girls_award/index.html|script-title=ja: Girls Award 2009 グラビアアイドルも多数出演！豪華ファッションショー＆ライブイベント！|accessdate=2016-10-24|publisher=Asuka International Corp.|language=Japanese}}</ref> In 2010, from Girls Award 2010, the location was moved to Yoyogi National Gymnasium.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mdpr.jp/gal/detail/368302|script-title=ja:人気「Popteen」モデルも「Girls Award 2010」に出演|date=2010-05-24|accessdate=2016-10-24|publisher=modelpress|language=Japanese}}</ref> From January 25 to 27, 2012, a collaboration event was held with [[South Korea]]n television [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] featuring the fashion show and [[K-pop]] music.<ref name="jpnews20120126">{{cite web|url=http://jpnews.kr/sub_read.html?uid=12730&section=sc1|script-title=ko:2% 아쉬웠던 韓日패션교류쇼 'KISS'|date=2012-01-26|accessdate=2016-10-24|publisher=JPNews|language=Korean}}</ref> In 2014, the first overseas event with [[A-Nation]] was held in [[Taiwan]].<ref name="oricon20140913">{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/music/special/2014/a-nation_taiwan/livereport_jp.html|script-title=ja:a-nation taiwan『史上初の台湾公演をレポート！』-ORICON STYLE ミュージック|accessdate=2016-10-24|publisher=oricon ME|language=Japanese}}</ref> On April 9, 2016, during GirlsAward 2016 S/S, [[Instagram]]'s CEO [[Kevin Systrom]] appeared on the stage and made a [[selfie]] performance with [[Haruna Kojima]], a member of [[AKB48]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mdpr.jp/news/detail/1577088|script-title=ja:ダレノガレ明美・ラブリ・玉城ティナら「Instagram」創業者とセルフィーで交流＜GirlsAward 2016 S／S＞|date=2016-04-10|accessdate=2016-10-24|publisher=modelpress|language=Japanese}}</ref>
