{{italic title}}
'''''Rest Energy''''' is a 1980 [[performance art]] piece created and performed by then-performance artist duo [[Marina Abramović]] and [[Ulay]] and recorded in [[Amsterdam]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pomeranz-collection.com/?q=node/39|title=Marina Abramovic & Ulay|publisher=Pomeranz Collection|accessdate=Feb 10, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=http://www.phaidon.com/agenda/art/picture-galleries/2010/march/22/documenting-the-performance-art-of-marina-abramovi-in-pictures/?idx=9|title=Documenting the performance art of Marina Abramović in pictures|page=9|publisher=Phaidon|accessdate=Feb 10, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dublincity.ie/libcat/02_Catalogue/02_005_TitleInformation.aspx?searchTerm=&searchTerm2=&searchTerm3=&searchTerm4=&searchType=&Page=1&media=&branch=&authority=&language=&junior=&rcn=EX00132412&fr=tl|archive-url=https://archive.is/20150207061903/http://www.dublincity.ie/libcat/02_Catalogue/02_005_TitleInformation.aspx?searchTerm=&searchTerm2=&searchTerm3=&searchTerm4=&searchType=&Page=1&media=&branch=&authority=&language=&junior=&rcn=EX00132412&fr=tl|dead-url=yes|archive-date=February 7, 2015|title=Rosc '80, the poetry of vision; an international exhibition of modern art and Chinese painting [shown in the rooms of the School of Architecture University College Dublin and in the National Gallery of Ireland, July to September 1980]|publisher=Dublin City Public Libraries|accessdate=Feb 10, 2015}}</ref> Four minutes in duration, Abramović has described it as one of two of the most difficult pieces she has ever done, saying {{quote|I was not in charge. In ''Rest Energy'' we actually held an arrow on the weight of our bodies, and the arrow is pointed right into my heart. We had two small microphones near our hearts, so we could hear our heartbeats. As our performance was progressing, heartbeats were becoming more and more intense, and though it lasted just four minutes and ten seconds, I’m telling you, for me it was forever. It was a performance about the complete and total trust.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abramovic.garageccc.com/en/works/7#part-7|title=Works With Ulay|publisher=Garage Center for Contemporary Culture, Moscow|accessdate=Feb 10, 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150221154621/http://abramovic.garageccc.com/en/works/7#part-7|archivedate=2015-02-21|df=}}</ref>}}

The piece is in the collection of the [[Netherlands Media Art Institute]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://artforum.com/video/id=25124&mode=large&page_id=12|title=Video: Marina Abramović and Ulay, Rest Energy, 1980. (Excerpt)|publisher=artforum.com|accessdate=Feb 10, 2015}}</ref>

