{{Infobox newspaper |name = The Observer (Uganda) |logo = |image = |caption = |type = [[Weekly newspaper]] |publisher = Observer Media Limited |editor = [[Richard M Kavuma]] |founded = 2004 |language = [[English (language)|English]] |headquarters = [[Kampala]], [[Uganda]] |website = http://www.observer.ug/ }}
'''''The Weekly Observer''''' is a [[Uganda]]n weekly newspaper headquartered in [[Kampala]]. It is one of the largest privately owned papers in the country.<ref>Robert Barlas, Jui Lin Yong, ''Uganda (Cultures of the World)'' ([[Marshall Cavendish]], 2nd ed., 2010), {{ISBN|978-0761448594}}, p. 99. [https://books.google.com/books?id=T3RYYPSq8JoC&lpg=PA99&dq=observer%20newspaper%20uganda&pg=PA99#v=onepage&q=observer%20newspaper%20uganda&f=false Excerpts available] at [[Google Books]].</ref> In 2007, its reporter [[Richard M Kavuma]] won the CNN Multichoice African Journalist of the Year award.<ref>[http://www.cnn.com/2007/WORLD/africa/07/22/african.journalist/ "Ugandan journalist scoops award"], [[CNN]], 24 July 2007. Retrieved 22 February 2013.</ref> The newspaper was founded in 2004 and celebrated 10 years of existence in March 2014.<ref>Pius Muteekani Katunzi, [http://allafrica.com/stories/201403240178.html?viewall=1 Uganda: The Observer, A Gamble That Has Paid Off] ''[[AllAfrica.com]]'' 28 March 2014. Retrieved 22 February 2013.</ref>
